<TITLE> Leaders issue messages of 'unity, peace' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 19(bdnews24.com)President Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and opposition leader Khaleda Zia issued Eid messages on Saturday with one theme in common, "unity and peace". The National Moon Sighting Committee sits on Sunday to announce which day Eid-ul-Fitr, the largest Muslim festival, will be celebratedon Monday or Tuesdaydepending on whether the Shawal moon is seen in the sky on the night. "Eid-ul-Fitr comes with a message of joy and rejoicings for mankind after a month of fasting," Zillur Rahman said in his message. "The poor and the rich stand together in a bond of unity and brotherhood on the day. The message of Eid-ul-Fitr is eternal for the building of a peaceful society". Sheikh Hasina message also spoke of peace and equality. "Eid teaches a lesson of peace, cordiality and brotherhood. All differences disappear on the occasion. The bond of equality, amity and harmony bind men together." She urged all to take lessons from Eid for individual, social and national life. Khaleda Zia remembered the poor and deprived in her message. "Eidul-Fitr is not just a time for festivity. Removing social disparity, overcoming the line of divide and remembering the spirit that 'we are all for all' are the lessons of the occasion." "It is our duty as Muslims to extend a helping hand to the poor, neglected and deprived." She said, "High prices of essentials and economic crisis in the country will make it difficult for many to enjoy Eid." She urged the rich to help the poor as much as possible. bdnew
